# Worker Auth + CORS Contract

- Keep browser CORS behavior explicit and testable for `OPTIONS`, `GET`, and `POST`.
- If frontend uses `credentials: include`, Worker responses must include:
  - explicit `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` (not wildcard)
  - `Access-Control-Allow-Credentials: true`
- Keep `Vary: Origin` when allowlist-based origin handling is used.

## Hybrid Auth Rule

- Support token-auth path and credential path without breaking existing clients.
- Auth mode changes must preserve non-destructive error handling client-side.
- Never log raw secrets/tokens.

## Verification

- Run `scripts/simulate_shopping_list_dual_device.py`.
- Validate live preflight headers with explicit `OPTIONS` request.
- Confirm `/health` reflects auth/cors capability metadata.
